brand.fix:
Add a text-based regex fallback as the last resort:
    if (!product.brand) {
        const bodyText = document.body ? document.body.innerText : '';
        const storeMatch = bodyText.match(/Visit the ([\w\s]+) Store/);
        if (storeMatch) product.brand = storeMatch[1].trim();
    }
This catches 'Visit the Nintendo Store' from anywhere in the page text, regardless of DOM structure.
